<br>
For those who have never played UO, you could very well get to the highest levels of character development (UO not really having levels in the EQ sense) without killing a single monster. This didn't mean it was *easier* than killing monsters, just a different way of going about it - chopping wood, mining, honing your skills... and in the earlier days, avoiding PKs... It was also possible for two characters of differing levels to meaningfully play together, too.<br>
<br>
There's no reason a craftsman class wouldn't work. There's no reason they wouldn't have *something* to contribute to combat, but there's also no reason why SoE couldn't add viable paths of development OTHER than killing mobs to get bigger sticks to kill bigger mobs. That style of play was old on the DikuMUDs Everquest ripped its gameplay from, and expanding it out to something the size of EQ has shown just how boring and stupid it can get at times<br>
<br>
That said, I still want killing mobs for big sticks to still be viable *too*... I'm just glad that SoE is, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>apparently</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, willing to explore other ways of building a MMOG.<br>
